  "text": "HomeShoppingBrand BioIt's endorsed by the National Eczema Association.Photo: Courtesy of Tower 28Tower 28Headquarters: Los Angeles, CAE-commerce: tower28beauty.comSocial Media: Instagram / TiktokWhat: A skin-care and makeup brand developed for those with sensitive skin.Price Range: $15-$34Founder: Amy LiuOrigin Story: Founder Amy Liu served for nearly 20 years as an executive at some of the fastest growing beauty brands, but as an eczema sufferer, she couldn't enjoy the best part: trying out products. And so she launched Tower 28 in 2019, as a beauty brand inclusive of all skin tones, skin types, budgets and beauty philosophies. With the message that \"#ItsOkayToBeSensitive,\" Tower 28 is the first and only beauty brand to adhere to the National Eczema Association's guidelines, with zero irritating ingredients and formulas that are \"100% safe for sensitive skin.\" It's also \"clean,\" vegan and rigorously dermatologist-tested. Scroll to ContinueRecommended ArticlesStockists: Sephora, Credo BeautyHero Products: SOS Spray ($28)PR Representation: Note PRHow to get in touch: caitlin@note-pr.comWant your brand featured? Hit the link below.Please note: Occasionally, we use affiliate links on our site. This in no way affects our editorial decision-making.From emerging startups to Fortune 500 companies, brands are building awareness, driving sales and gaining followers by partnering with Fashionista. Discover our unique digital offerings here.Subscribe to Our Newsletter",
